==Korean==
===Noun===
'''바다코끼리''' (''bada-kokkiri'') (''literally, "sea elephant"'') 
# [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[sea horse]] (''mammal''), [[walrus]] cf. Czech [[mrož]], Estonian [[merihobu]], Finnish [[mursu]], French [[morse]], Spanish [[morsa]] (''cf. Latin [[mare]] "sea", Korean [[물]] (mul, mur) "water, sea"'')  

====Synonyms====
*[[해상]] ([[海象]], ''haesang'') (''literally, "sea elephant"'') [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[walrus]], [[sea horse]] (''mammal'') 
*[[해마]] ([[海馬]], ''haema'') (''literally, "sea horse"'')  [[sea horse]] (''mammal''), [[sea elephant]], [[elephant seal]], [[walrus]] (''allegedly from inversion of Old Norse [[hrosshvalr]], "horse-whale"'')

====See also====
*[[물개]] (''mul-gae'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[dog]]"'') [[ear]]ed [[seal]], [[fur]] [[seal]], [[sea lion]] 
*[[물범]] (''mul-beom'') (''literally, "[[water]] [[tiger]]"'') [[hair]] [[seal]] (''earless'') 

 
